author: Mia PGB
text:
My husband and I were gaining weight and we had no excuse. It was the health issues we were experiencing that prompted us to go on a fitness plan. Anytime Fitness Sembawang and their personal trainer Nina helped us a lot in getting the results we wanted.

The gym is well equipped and ventilated. All the staff, from the managers, trainers and maintenance are super friendly, approachable, and very supportive from day one. The gym itself and the equipment are really clean, which we greatly appreciated. I was never uncomfortable whenever I was there. The gym being a stone's throw away from our work place was also a plus.

Nina is an amazing trainer. I am grateful for her patience, support and encouragement. She has set a regime for us to follow that worked very well. We were able to get to our fitness goals with hard work, dedication and determination not only by me and my husband but with Nina as well. She was with us althroughout and has been a huge part of us being healthy. We only have fond memories of you, Nina!

The benefit of being with Anytime Fitness is that you can use any of their gyms as long as you have your fob with you. We lived in Ang Mo Kio and it was never troublesome for us to visit AF's other branches during our off days and away from Sembawang. This is applicable internationally, too.

Unfortunately, we had to say goodbye to this amazing gym because we migrated to Australia in January this year. Although our journey with  Anytime Fitness Sembawang was short, it was definitely a fruitful and enjoyable experience. We are planning to sign up with AF near our place soon.

Thank you for the wonderful experience, AF Sembawang! We are missing this awesome gym a lot! üí™

Regards to everyone!

Mia & August

author: Akhil
text:
Title: Terrible Experience - Avoid Anytime Fitness at All Costs!

I recently had the most disappointing and frustrating experience with Anytime Fitness, and I feel compelled to share it with others to prevent them from going through the same ordeal. Before joining the gym, they recommended that I take a 1.5-year membership without mentioning the existence of a notice period. They also assured me that they would assist in holding my membership during periods when I needed to be away from Singapore. Unfortunately, the reality turned out to be far from what was promised.

Due to unforeseen circumstances, I lost my job and had to return to India. As requested by Anytime Fitness, I provided them with all the required documentation, including a one way air ticket, a photo of my passport seal upon entering India, and a screenshot of my location on Google Maps. Despite complying with their demands, after the third month, they suddenly informed me that they couldn't extend my membership any further and resumed charging me.

To make matters worse, my membership had already expired six months ago, well beyond the initially agreed 1.5-year duration. When I requested to cancel my membership, they insisted on an additional paid month as a notice period, even though my financial situation was dire due to the lack of job opportunities and the high cost of living in Singapore. I explained my predicament, but they callously charged me twice, a total of $31, claiming that the cancellation couldn't be processed.

Aside from the horrendous customer service, the gym itself is far from satisfactory. The lack of sufficient equipment and the overwhelming number of people make it nearly impossible to have a productive workout, especially during peak hours. I strongly advise anyone looking for a gym in the Nordcomm or Gymbox area to consider alternative options, as the experience at Anytime Fitness is simply not worth the trouble.

Save yourself the frustration, disappointment, and unnecessary expenses by avoiding Anytime Fitness at all costs. There are definitely better gyms in the area that offer superior customer service and a more conducive workout environment.

Overall, Anytime Fitness Sembawang provides a convivial and safe space for both seasoned and amateur gym-goers, there is really little judgement which is very important for anyone to start or maintain a good exercising habit. The staff members are all very welcoming and always present to provide help and guidance. More importantly, they always keep the gym clean and tidy, please keep up with the awesome work!

text: Inquired about signing up through their whatsapp and the other person was very thorough in explaining the price breakdown. Immediately made an appointment to head down to sign up. She seems approachable and is able to answer and assist any doubt easily. Went for the Body composition machine and got directed to Trainer Noorlina, whom has given a full, detailed explanation on the scans and result, which allows newbie to understand the results in a simplest form. Very knowledgeable and has provided many recommendations and ways for us to work towards our goals based on our capabilities. Overall, it is a great and welcoming experience for someone who has very little knowledge and wants to start working out!

It's more spacious but they took the toilet out so have to go use the mall toilet.
Water dispenser pressure also is low.

I am surprised by the staff friendly especially to Ben Huang who has share with my husband and i the Anytime Fitness app and even went the extra mile to help me to call up Greenwich when we cannot sign in. But one thing I'm upset about is that I am unable to book for classes online as I'm not a member of this club but Ben assure me that I could have access to the class system as long as I check in here more frequently and he will update me when I'm a member here! author: Kanna P
text:
Disappointing. After weeks of notifying staff that the airconditioning is off after midnight, making the conditions of those who train during those hours very unsatisfying, nothing has changed. Occasionally even see trainers come in at 7am and notice that the airconditioned has been turned off the whole time and just giggle. Not sure how difficult it is to keep the AC on after midnight or at least notify people that it will be kept off. So far just empty assurances. Not recommended at all for anyone planning to train after midnight, inconsistent and poorly managed. Staff will give you a hard time if you squat without shoes in the power rack, but not do anything about anyone who doesnt rerack their weight or use towels.

Never posted a review in my life, but clearly none of the friendly feedback given so far has led to any change, so here you go.
